   161вҶ’## Environment Variables
   181вҶ’## Formatters
   196вҶ’### Custom formatters
   198вҶ’You can add custom formatters by extending the `debug.formatters` object.
   199вҶ’For example, if you wanted to add support for rendering a Buffer as hex with
   200вҶ’`%h`, you could do something like:
   201вҶ’
   202вҶ’```js
   203вҶ’const createDebug = require('debug')
   204вҶ’createDebug.formatters.h = (v) => {
   205вҶ’  return v.toString('hex')
   206вҶ’}
   207вҶ’
   208вҶ’// вҖҰelsewhere
   209вҶ’const debug = createDebug('foo')
   210вҶ’debug('this is hex: %h', new Buffer('hello world'))
   211вҶ’//   foo this is hex: 68656c6c6f20776f726c6421 +0ms
   212вҶ’```
   213вҶ’
